her's Son]]''\n| DC Sue Upton\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2012\u2013present\n| ''[[Last Tango in Halifax]]''\n| Gillian Buttershaw\n| 24 episodes<br/>Nominated\u2014[[BAFTA TV Awards|BAFTA TV Award for Best Supporting Actress]]<br/>Nominated\u2014[[Satellite Award for Best Supporting Actress&nbsp;\u2013 Series, Miniseries or Television Film]]\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Prisoners' Wives]]''\n| DCI Jo Fontaine\n| 4 episodes\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Heading Out]]''\n| Justine\n| 6 episodes\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Scott & Bailey]]''\n| Helen Bartlett\n| 4 episodes\n|-\n| 2014\n|  ''[[Babylon (TV series)|Babylon]]''\n| Sharon Franklin, Assistant Commissioner\n| 7 episodes (main role)\n|-\n|2015\u2014present\n|''[[Unforgotten]]''\n|DCI Cassie Stuart\n|3 series (18 episodes, main role)\n|-\n| 2015\n|''[[River (TV series)|River]]''\n|DS Jackie \"Stevie\" Stevenson\n|6 episodes (main role)\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Collateral (TV series)|Collateral]]''\n| Jane Oliver\n| Miniseries (4 episodes, main role)\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Inside No 9]]''\n| Harriet\n| Episode \"To Have and to Hold\" series 4\n|-\n| 2018\u2014present\n|''[[The Split (TV series)|The Split]]''\n| Hannah Stern\n| 12 episodes (main role)\n|}\n\n===Video games===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Voice role\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[The Witcher 2: Assassins of Kings]]''\n| S\u00edle de Tansarville\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[007 Legends]]''\n| [[Tracy Bond|Teresa di Vicenzo]]\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt]]''\n| S\u00edle de Tansarville\n|}\n\n===Audio===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year \n! Title \n! Role \n|-\n| 2002 \n| BBC's ''Neuromancer'' \n| Molly \n|-\n| 2013\u2013present \n| ''Doctor Who'' \n| Liv Chenka \n|}\n\n==Theatre credits==\n* ''Relocated'' \u2013 [[Royal Court Theatre]] London (2008)\n* ''Gethsemane'' \u2013 [[Royal National Theatre|National Theatre]] London (2008/9)\n* ''Season's Greetings'' \u2013 [[Royal National Theatre|National Theatre]] London (2010/11)\n* ''Di and Viv and Rose'' \u2013 [[